      • popUpAddCustomerSorF

        public static void popUpAddCustomerSorF​(java.lang.String SorF,
                                        java.lang.String cName,
                                        java.lang.String YorN,
                                        java.lang.String button)
        This creates a specific popup window for the add/delete of a customer to the database
        Parameters:
        SorF - stands for success or fail. will populate the error message in the popup
        cName - stands for customer Name. will populate the error message in the popup
        YorN - stands for Yes or no. will populate the error message in the popup
        button - Sets the popup button "OK" text to the language selection of the user

        Parameters:

      • popUpWindow

                               java.lang.String message,
                               java.lang.String title,
                               java.lang.String button)
        A generic popup window to use for small/unlikely errors
        Parameters:
        input - is the error type itself to add to the actual display message
        message - is combined with the input parameter to make a complete message
        title - sets the title of the popup window
        button - sets the text of the button
